ğŸŸ¦ US3 â€“ Display a persistent action bar with BACK, VALIDATE and NEXT buttons

User Story

As a coach
I want a persistent action bar with contextual primary actions
So that I can explicitly validate certain actions before moving to the next step of the process

â¸»

Description

A persistent action bar is displayed above the footer on all steps of the Return Hardware journey.

The action bar contains:
	â€¢	BACK button (always visible)
	â€¢	A contextual primary action button, displayed one at a time:
	â€¢	VALIDATE: used to confirm an in-step action (e.g. add selected equipment to a cart)
	â€¢	NEXT: used to navigate to the next step of the stepper

â¸»

Behavior (Key Rules)
	1.	VALIDATE and NEXT are mutually exclusive
	â€¢	Only one primary action button is visible at any time
	2.	VALIDATE behavior
	â€¢	Displayed when the current step requires an explicit validation action
	â€¢	Example: validating the selection of equipment and adding it to a cart
	â€¢	Clicking VALIDATE:
	â€¢	validates the action
	â€¢	updates the internal state (e.g. cart updated)
	â€¢	does NOT move to the next step
	3.	NEXT behavior
	â€¢	Displayed only after the required validation action has been successfully completed
	â€¢	Used exclusively to move to the next step of the stepper
	4.	State handling
	â€¢	VALIDATE and NEXT are disabled if required conditions are not met
	â€¢	BACK never resets previously entered or validated data
	5.	Persistence
	â€¢	The action bar is always visible
	â€¢	Header and action bar remain visible during error handling (modal or toast)

â¸»

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN I am on a step requiring in-step validation
THEN the primary action button displayed is "VALIDATE"
AND the "NEXT" button is not visible

WHEN I click "VALIDATE"
AND the validation is successful
THEN the validated action is applied (e.g. equipment added to cart)
AND the primary action button switches to "NEXT"

WHEN the primary action button is "NEXT"
AND I click it
THEN I am navigated to the next step of the stepper

WHEN validation conditions are not met
THEN the primary action button (VALIDATE or NEXT) is disabled

WHEN I click "BACK"
THEN I return to the previous step
AND all previously validated data is preserved

WHEN an error modal or toast is displayed
THEN the header and action bar remain visible


